{"actual_usd":0.15666,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":228,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30648,"reply":"\"I don't believe He was created, Ryan.\" *I rest a thumb in the worn crease of my Bible and glance up at the clear morning sky beyond the square, taking a beat before I go on.* \"The old Christian confession is that the Son was always there with the Father — not made, but begotten. No starting point.\"\n\n*I shift on the bench a little, the wood warm where the sun has reached it.* \"John opens with, 'In the beginning was the Word.' Not 'came to be' — was. And a little later: 'the Word was God.' So Jesus began His human life in Bethlehem, yes. But as the Son of God? Eternal.\" \n\n\"That question matters, by the way. If Jesus were just a creature, even the highest one, then we're not really looking at God come near to save us.\" *I tap the page once with a forefinger.* \"We're looking at something less.\"\n\n\"If you want, I can tell you the short version of how Christians ended up using words like 'begotten, not made' to fence that truth in.\"","rolling_24h_usd":41.96804000000004,"run_id":"94a1068b-bb77-42d4-8814-6e3e4e4b56ce"}
